reenFromWeb?topicID=441.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   mages solo?</span><hr size=1> can mages solo all the way up through the lvl's?  i got a 30 mage right now and obviusly can solo anything blue.  just wanted to know if i can expect the same power all the way up. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 390<br> <font color=#333333>(2/6/03 5:57:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=441.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: mages solo?</span><hr size=1> I soloed my 2nd mage from 1-60th level with no problems whatsoever.  After that, things get tough. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elfnom>Elfnom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#333333>(2/6/03 8:51:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=441.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Easy to 61</span><hr size=1> <br>
  I've solo'd to 60 and have my exp bar full ready to ding into 61 when I get all the 61 spells.  No problem to solo to 61 at all.  The shrooms in FG will probably still be fair experience even at 61, so I can see it would be easy to solo up to level 62.  After 62, it looks like it gets pretty tough to solo for exp.  You'd have to get info from someone in the 62 level to know for sure.  <br>
<br>
  Elfnom<br>
  60 mage <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=variathemage>Varia the mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 167<br> <font color=#333333>(2/7/03 10:58:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=441.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: mages solo?</span><hr size=1> If you are determined, mages can solo to 65.  It really isn't worth it once you hit 62 though.  With PoP, I've found it better to group in the new zones rather than try to solo in the old ones or even solo the lowest mobs in the new zones.  I soloed a few rats in Disease when I was 62.  They hit for about 260, but their HP aren't too bad so its just a question of burning them down quick enough.  The exp wasn't as good as I would have thought.<br>
<br>
Soloing is really all about knowing where to hunt at what level and to a lesser degree, what tactics to use at each spot. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=108671">Varia Darselai</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Arch Convoker</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=swagman@themagicianstower>swagman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(2/8/03 3:24:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=441.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   soloing</span><hr size=1> I have soloed my mage til 61. at 62 im gonna have to play with the common people because everything soloable will now be light blue. And dont believe the hysteria. Other then POP there is better exp soloing, as long as you chain cast. A mage can kill and pull as fast as a full grp. at velks i could chain pull and kill the mob just as fast as a grp of six until they turned lt blue. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khalendor>Khalendor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 209<br> <font color=#333333>(2/8/03 9:48:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=441.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: soloing</span><hr size=1> You can still solo the druids in PoS with the 61 air pet, just watch out for the adds. <p>Khalendor Dayze</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lordgojirax>LordGojirax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 455<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 7:26:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=441.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojhead.jpg width=98 height=126></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: soloing</span><hr size=1> How much Solo exp would the shrooms in FG give to a level 52 Epic Mage? (Would this be a better place to kill than say Flies in PoD?)<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojirax.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 416<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 7:34:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=441.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: soloing</span><hr size=1> The epic doesn't fare so well against the shrooms, and you can't single pull them at 52.  You really need gvoc:earth to resist the shroom spells, and you need to be level 60 to single pull them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lordgojirax>LordGojirax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 458<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 8:25:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=441.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojhead.jpg width=98 height=126></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: soloing</span><hr size=1> 3 Mage friends of mine in my guild used to farm AA's there all the time using Epic. The damage shield does a tremendous amount of their damage.. I'm just wondering how the exp stacks up.<br>
<br>
